headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving returned from his personal “pause” to score 37 points in his first game with Kevin Durant and James Harden but the new-look, star-studded Brooklyn Nets gave up 42 to Collin Sexton and lost 147-135 in double overtime to the Cleveland...
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving returns, but new-look Nets beaten by Cavs in 2 OTs

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis posted season-high totals of 27 points and 12 rebounds in leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 124-111 victory at Indiana on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis' big night leads Mavericks past Pacers 124-112

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 42 points and 10 rebounds and Tobias Harris scored 22 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 117-109 win over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
— Trae Young scored 38 points, John Collins had 31, and the Atlanta Hawks rallied to beat Jerami Grant and the Detroit Pistons 123-115 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young has 38, Collins adds 31 as Hawks beat Pistons in OT

headlines.description: — Kendrick Nunn scored 28 points and the injury-plagued Miami Heat pulled away in the second half for a 111-102 win over the Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night.
— Cole Anthony hit a hurried 3-pointer at the buzzer and the Orlando Magic stunned the Minnesota Timberwolves 97-96 on Wednesday night to stop a six-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony hits buzzer-beating 3, Magic edge Timberwolves 97-96

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had season highs with 26 points and 17 rebounds and the Phoenix Suns beat the Houston Rockets 109-103 on Wednesday night to end a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton has season-high 26 points, Suns beat Rockets 109-103

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 26 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists, and the Golden State Warriors beat the San Antonio Spurs 121-99 on Wednesday night while honoring new Vice President Kamala Harris and her Oakland roots.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors honor VP Kamala Harris in win over Spurs

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 32 points, Paul George added 19 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Sacramento Kings 115-96 on Wednesday night for their season-high fifth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Kings 115-96 for season-high 5th straight win

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers
